{
    "publish_date": "2013-10-08T20:00:53.000Z", 
    "video_length": "PT3M9S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Look, we&#39;ve always known that\nEinstein was better than us.", 
            "dur": "3.177", 
            "start": "0"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But now we know why.", 
            "dur": "0.833", 
            "start": "3.177"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Anthony here from D News.", 
            "dur": "1.041", 
            "start": "10.609"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And we are constantly hearing\nabout Einstein&#39;s brain.", 
            "dur": "2.63", 
            "start": "11.65"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It was removed about eight\nhours after his death,", 
            "dur": "2.34", 
            "start": "14.28"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and we&#39;ve just been\npoking at it ever since,", 
            "dur": "2.44", 
            "start": "16.62"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "looking for the differences that\nmade it such a brilliant mind.", 
            "dur": "3.43", 
            "start": "19.06"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And a study recently published\nin the journal, Brain", 
            "dur": "2.64", 
            "start": "22.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "thinks that they&#39;ve\nfound the answer.", 
            "dur": "1.56", 
            "start": "25.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it&#39;s in the corpus callosum,\nthe body&#39;s largest bundle", 
            "dur": "3.58", 
            "start": "26.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "of neuronal fibers\nthat sits underneath", 
            "dur": "2.41", 
            "start": "30.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "your cerebral cortex.", 
            "dur": "1.43", 
            "start": "32.68"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Among its functions\nis making sure", 
            "dur": "2.58", 
            "start": "34.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that both halves\nof the brain can", 
            "dur": "1.95", 
            "start": "36.69"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "communicate with each other.", 
            "dur": "1.22", 
            "start": "38.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Now, we&#39;ve talked about the\nleft brain, right brain myth", 
            "dur": "2.333", 
            "start": "39.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and lateralization before.", 
            "dur": "1.377", 
            "start": "42.193"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Spark Notes version--\nthere&#39;s no such thing", 
            "dur": "2.03", 
            "start": "43.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as a left or right brain person.", 
            "dur": "1.449", 
            "start": "45.6"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You are a beautiful,\nunique snowflake", 
            "dur": "1.541", 
            "start": "47.049"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that can do anything you want,\nthanks to practice and neural", 
            "dur": "2.8", 
            "start": "48.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "plasticity.", 
            "dur": "0.71", 
            "start": "51.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "However, the things\nyou do are controlled", 
            "dur": "2.707", 
            "start": "52.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by different parts of the brain.", 
            "dur": "1.333", 
            "start": "54.807"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if those parts\nare on different sides", 
            "dur": "2.29", 
            "start": "56.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and need to work\ntogether, they&#39;ve", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "58.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "got to go through the\ncorpus callosum to do it.", 
            "dur": "2.58", 
            "start": "60.23"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Einstein&#39;s corpus callosum had\nextremely thick connections", 
            "dur": "3.67", 
            "start": "62.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "between the halves of three\nvery interesting brain", 
            "dur": "2.79", 
            "start": "66.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "regions-- his\nprefrontal cortex, which", 
            "dur": "2.32", 
            "start": "69.27"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "controls abstract thinking\nand decision-making,", 
            "dur": "2.38", 
            "start": "71.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "his parietal lobe, which is all\nabout sense and motor function,", 
            "dur": "3.54", 
            "start": "73.97"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and his visual\ncortex, for seeing.", 
            "dur": "2.75", 
            "start": "77.51"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The thicker connections could\nbe responsible for lower", 
            "dur": "2.55", 
            "start": "80.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "lateralization of brain\nactivity and at least partially", 
            "dur": "3.06", 
            "start": "82.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "explain why he was so\nbrilliant, which is interesting,", 
            "dur": "2.53", 
            "start": "85.87"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because lower\nlateralization in the brain", 
            "dur": "2.14", 
            "start": "88.4"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "has also been linked to\nschizophrenia and psychopathy.", 
            "dur": "3.02", 
            "start": "90.54"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So how do you get\nbrain like Einstein&#39;s?", 
            "dur": "2.62", 
            "start": "93.56"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Last week, I talked a little\nbit about neural plasticity", 
            "dur": "2.34", 
            "start": "96.18"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and how the more you use\na part of your brain,", 
            "dur": "2.05", 
            "start": "98.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the stronger it gets and the\nthicker its connections become.", 
            "dur": "2.5", 
            "start": "100.57"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So in theory, to\nthink like Einstein,", 
            "dur": "2.43", 
            "start": "103.07"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;ve got to do\nactivities that will", 
            "dur": "1.7", 
            "start": "105.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "keep your corpus\ncallosum active and use", 
            "dur": "2.68", 
            "start": "107.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "both hemispheres of\nyour brain at once.", 
            "dur": "1.87", 
            "start": "109.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Multiple studies have\nshown that musicians", 
            "dur": "2.09", 
            "start": "111.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "tend to use their\nwhole brain more.", 
            "dur": "1.52", 
            "start": "113.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Einstein himself\nwas a violinist.", 
            "dur": "1.99", 
            "start": "115.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So maybe taking up an instrument\nor music lessons could help.", 
            "dur": "3.02", 
            "start": "117.35"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Handedness is connected\nto lateralization.", 
            "dur": "2.24", 
            "start": "120.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So by being\nleft-handed, I&#39;m using", 
            "dur": "2.35", 
            "start": "122.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the right part of\nmy motor cortex.", 
            "dur": "1.84", 
            "start": "124.96"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A 2004 study in Nature\nshowed that juggling", 
            "dur": "3.04", 
            "start": "126.8"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "could help me strengthen\nup my whole brain activity", 
            "dur": "2.4", 
            "start": "129.84"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by requiring me\nto use both hands.", 
            "dur": "2.22", 
            "start": "132.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Just using your\nnon-dominant hand", 
            "dur": "1.67", 
            "start": "134.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "throughout the day for things\nlike brushing your teeth", 
            "dur": "2.25", 
            "start": "136.13"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "could potentially\ndo the same thing.", 
            "dur": "1.82", 
            "start": "138.38"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Logic and math puzzles are\ngood, because number estimates", 
            "dur": "3.14", 
            "start": "140.2"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and comparison use both\nhalves of your parietal lobe.", 
            "dur": "2.47", 
            "start": "143.34"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if you&#39;re terrible\nat them, like me,", 
            "dur": "1.834", 
            "start": "145.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it means you also get to\nwork out your amygdala, yor", 
            "dur": "2.166", 
            "start": "147.644"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "ventral medial prefrontal\ncortex, and your limbic system", 
            "dur": "2.96", 
            "start": "149.81"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by flying into a rage.", 
            "dur": "1.82", 
            "start": "152.77"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Just remember to\nflip the desk over", 
            "dur": "2.14", 
            "start": "154.59"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with your non-dominant hand.", 
            "dur": "1.7", 
            "start": "156.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I have some issues.", 
            "dur": "0.81", 
            "start": "158.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Anyway, an unanswered\nquestion here", 
            "dur": "1.86", 
            "start": "159.24"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is whether Einstein was\nborn with a more developed", 
            "dur": "2.42", 
            "start": "161.1"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "corpus callosum to\nbegin with, which", 
            "dur": "1.91", 
            "start": "163.52"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would have given this sort\nof thinking a head start.", 
            "dur": "2.18", 
            "start": "165.43"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "I also cannot tell you with\na straight face that brushing", 
            "dur": "2.86", 
            "start": "167.61"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "your teeth with the wrong hand\nor playing the ukelele is going", 
            "dur": "2.954", 
            "start": "170.47"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to turn you into the\nnext great thinker.", 
            "dur": "1.666", 
            "start": "173.424"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But making conscious\ndecisions to learn, adapt,", 
            "dur": "2.92", 
            "start": "175.09"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and be creative\nevery day can&#39;t hurt.", 
            "dur": "1.631", 
            "start": "178.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What do you think?", 
            "dur": "0.749", 
            "start": "179.641"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Was Einstein born better, or\ndid he make himself that way?", 
            "dur": "3.12", 
            "start": "180.39"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Let me know down below, and\nsubscribe for more D News.", 
            "dur": "3.84", 
            "start": "183.51"
        }
    ], 
